768. nomina. Quinquatrus or Quinquatria, which ac- cording to Varro was so called because it came five days after the Ides. It also lasted five days. So, at Tusculum, there were festivals called Sexatrus and Septimatrus, on the 6th and 7th days after the Ides. The Quinquatrus majores were the Easter holidays. Of. J uv. X. 115. There was a smaller festival of the same name in June.
